	(text_box "Since the LiPo battery voltage can drop below the desired system voltage of 3.3V and the input voltage can be as high as 5V, it is recommended to use a buck-boost regulator.\n\nThere is also a significant amount of capacitance on the output rail, so it is recommended to use a regulator with soft-start functionality.\n\nTo reduce noise on the system voltage rail, chain a low-dropout regulator (LDO) with a high PSRR."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 113.03 63.5 0)
		(size 209.55 38.1)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2.54 2.54)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "1f388145-4b2d-4d77-a834-1574ae040178")
	)
	(text_box "The regulator is capable of sourcing\n2 A @ V_{IN} = 3 V and 4 A @ V_{IN} = 5V.\n\nThe MCU draws approximately 100 mA in the worst-case scenario.\nThe modem draws approximately 500 mA in the worst-case scenario.\n\nThe values for the inductor and the feedback resistors are generated\nby the Texas Instruments' WEBENCH Power Designer tool with\nthe following parameters:\n- V_{IN}_MIN = 3.0 V\n- V_{IN}_MAX = 5.0 V\n- V_{OUT} = 3.7 V\n- I_{OUT}_MAX = 2 A"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 127 114.3 0)
		(size 76.2 31.75)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2e473f7e-2011-4c62-bc73-fe077c4a6d65")
	)
	(text_box "For testing and measurement purposes, provide the following:\n- LED indicators to display the states of the voltage rails\n- The ability to easily perform current measurements\n- Test points to verify voltage rail levels"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 326.39 63.5 0)
		(size 77.47 38.1)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
